            <!--class dropdown shows item inside a menu (like navbar)
class="dropdown" → used for styling & functionality
It tells CSS/JS: “this item has a dropdown”
This is the main visible menu item
Text: Services
▾ → small arrow showing dropdown
href="#" → means it doesn’t go anywhere (just clickable)-->
            <li class="dropdown">
             <a href="#">Services ▾</a>
